      "anno_id": 1,
      "text": " By [17, Theorem 3.17], every automorphism of the poset  $(\\mathcal{G}_{\\infty}(H), \\subseteq)$  is induced by an invertible bounded linear or conjugate-linear operator. We explain why the same statement is not proved for the restrictions of adjacency preserving transformations on connected components of  $\\mathcal{G}_{\\infty}(H)$ .",
      "line_with_spans": [
        {
          "category_type": "text_span",
          "poly": [
            527.5,
            560,
            2022.5,
            560,
            2022.5,
