    },
    {
      "category_type": "plain_text",
      "poly": [
        522.5,
        765,
        2025,
        765,
        2025,
        1102.5,
        522.5,
        1102.5
      ],
      "ignore": false,
      "order": 5,
      "anno_id": 1,
      "text": " Let  $f$  be a bijective transformation of  $\\mathcal{G}_{\\infty}(H)$  preserving the adjacency relation in both directions and let  $C$  be a connected component of  $\\mathcal{G}_{\\infty}(H)$ . Without loss of generality, we can assume that  $f(C) = C$ . Denote by  $C_{\\pm}$  the set of all  $X \\in \\mathcal{G}_{\\infty}(H)$  such that  $X$  is a subspace of finite codimension in a certain element of  $C$  or  $X$  contains a certain element of  $C$  as a subspace of finite codimension. Then  $f$  can be uniquely extended to an automorphism of the poset  $(C_{\\pm}, \\subseteq)$  [\\[17, Theorem 2.19\\]](#page-9-1). This extension is denoted by the same symbol  $f$ .",
      "line_with_spans": [
        {
          "category_type": "text_span",
          "poly": [
            522.5,
            765,
            2025,
            765,
            2025,
            1102.5,
            522.5,
            1102.5
          ],
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "attribute": {
        "text_language": "",
        "text_background": "",
        "text_rotate": ""
      }
    },
    {
      "category_type": "plain_text",
      "poly": [
        525,
